-- Canadian pension fund to invest in India L&T unit
-- By Devidutta Tripathy
-- Mon Jun 23, 2014 12:18AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, June 23 (Reuters) - Larsen & Toubro Ltd <LART.NS>, India's biggest engineering and construction company, said on Monday a unit of Canada Pension Plan Investment Board had agreed to invest an initial 10 billion rupees ($168 million) in its infrastructure development arm.

The Canadian pension fund will invest a further 10 billion rupees, or a higher amount, in L&T Infrastructure Development Projects Ltd (L&T IDPL) after 12 months of the first investment, L&T said in a statement.